# Help Desk Safety Rules

These rules are non-negotiable for any code under `reorg/src/app/(app)/help-desk/**`,
`reorg/src/app/api/helpdesk/**`, `reorg/src/components/helpdesk/**`,
`reorg/src/lib/helpdesk/**`, `reorg/src/lib/services/helpdesk-*`, or any new file
that touches `HelpdeskTicket`, `HelpdeskMessage`, `HelpdeskNote`,
`HelpdeskOutboundJob`, `HelpdeskTemplate`, `HelpdeskTag`, `HelpdeskNotification`,
`HelpdeskCheckpoint`, or `HelpdeskAuditLog`.

## Scope

- v1 Help Desk is **eBay only**. Do not add Shopify, BigCommerce, Telitetech, or
  any other marketplace as a message source or destination in this feature.
  Resend (External email) is the only non-eBay outbound transport allowed.
- Telitetech eBay (TT) is read-only for Help Desk in v1 — sync TT messages but
  never send replies through TT until explicitly approved.
- Pre-sales messages are explicitly in scope. Post-purchase messages are also
  in scope. Anything not derived from `GetMyMessages` is out of scope.

## No Deletion

- NEVER expose, implement, or call any "delete message" or "delete ticket"
  endpoint or service function. eBay has no message-delete API; we do not
  fabricate one client-side or in the database.
- `HelpdeskTicket.isArchived` and `HelpdeskTicket.isSpam` are the only
  hide-from-inbox mechanisms. Both must be reversible (reopen / unspam).
- `HelpdeskMessage` rows are append-only. Do not add UPDATE or DELETE paths
  to message bodies once written.
- Internal notes use soft-delete (`isDeleted`); never hard-delete a note row.

## Safe Mode is the Default

- `HELPDESK_SAFE_MODE=true` is the production default. In safe mode every
  outbound transport is blocked — eBay (AAQToPartner / RTQ) AND Resend.
- Outbound code must call `helpdeskFlags.safeMode` (or
  `helpdeskFlagsSnapshot().effectiveCanSendEbay` /
  `effectiveCanSendEmail`) before dispatching. Bypassing this is forbidden.
- A blocked send must log a `HelpdeskAuditLog` entry of action
  `OUTBOUND_BLOCKED` with the full block reason and the offending payload
  redacted of secrets.
- Safe mode banner must remain visible in the Help Desk header whenever the
  flag is on. Do not gate the banner behind any other condition.

## Outbound Sends

- All outbound flows go through the `HelpdeskOutboundJob` worker. Never call
  `sendHelpdeskReply()` or `sendExternalEmail()` directly from a route handler.
- Every send respects the per-message send delay; the user must be able to
  cancel the job before it dispatches. Status transitions
  (`PENDING → SENDING → SENT/FAILED/CANCELLED`) must be audit-logged.
- Outbound to eBay is always a reply. NEVER initiate an unsolicited
  `AddMemberMessageAAQToPartner` from this app — only RTQ replies in the
  context of an existing buyer thread are allowed in v1.
- Outbound attachments require `HELPDESK_ENABLE_ATTACHMENTS=true` AND
  composer mode `EXTERNAL`. eBay's RTQ has no file-attachment support;
  inline image URLs in the body are fine, but file uploads are not.

## Sync is Pull-Only

- The eBay sync worker (`helpdesk-ebay-sync.ts`) and its cron entry
  (`/api/cron/helpdesk-poll`) MUST be read-only with respect to eBay. Do
  not dispatch any send (`*RTQ`, `*AAQ*`, `MarkAsRead`, etc.) from a sync
  job. Read methods only.
- Sync writes only to `HelpdeskTicket`, `HelpdeskMessage`,
  `HelpdeskCheckpoint`, and `HelpdeskAuditLog` (where appropriate).
  It must never overwrite agent-authored fields (notes, tags, assignments,
  status set by an agent, snoozedUntil set by an agent, manual `kind`).
- Sync is idempotent on `(ebayMessageId)`. Re-running a poll must never
  create duplicate `HelpdeskMessage` rows.
- 2-stage polling is mandatory: a fast cron tick for active tickets and a
  slower tick for backfill / cold tickets. Never collapse them into one
  unbounded scan.

## Audit Logging

- Any state transition on a ticket (status, assignment, tag add/remove,
  archive, spam, snooze, reopen) MUST write a `HelpdeskAuditLog` row with
  `actorUserId`, `before`, `after`, and `action`.
- Any outbound attempt — successful, failed, blocked, or cancelled — MUST
  write a `HelpdeskAuditLog` row.
- Audit logs are append-only. Do not implement an update or delete path.
- Retain logs for at least 10 days (matches global app retention).

## Permissions

- Admin and Team Lead see every ticket and every action. Agent role sees
  every ticket but cannot modify integration credentials, write locks,
  feature flags, or templates owned by other users.
- Templates have a `scope` of `SHARED` (everyone) or `PERSONAL` (owner only).
  Do not let an agent edit or delete a template they don't own.

## Secrets

- Never log or return: eBay auth token, Resend API key, internal session
  cookie, raw `HelpdeskOutboundJob.payload` if it contains tokens.
- `helpdeskFlagsSnapshot()` is the only sanctioned way to surface flag
  state to the client. It must never include the underlying env strings.

## Backfill

- Initial backfill is capped at 180 days of eBay history. Do not raise
  this without an admin migration plan; eBay's `GetMyMessages` quota is
  not generous.
- Backfill runs incrementally via `HelpdeskCheckpoint.backfillDone`. Do
  not re-run a completed backfill on every cron tick.

## Testing

- Pure helpers in `reorg/src/lib/helpdesk/*.ts` must have unit tests in
  the same folder (`*.test.ts`, run with `npm test`).
- Outbound paths must have at least one test that asserts safe-mode blocks
  the send and produces an `OUTBOUND_BLOCKED` audit row.
- Tests must not hit the live eBay or Resend APIs. Use injected fakes.
